There is a big difference in the quote you provided vs the one being told by some mages here.  It was made before beastlords came into existance.
<br />

<br />
Verant/Sony has never said that (considering all pet classes, even beastlords) that mages are the supreme pet class and shall have a pet better than all else, bar none.  Or something to that effect.
<br />

<br />
Make it easier to digest by realizing that beastlords are a pet class, JUST AS MUCH AS MAGES ARE.  We are not, nor meant to be inferior to your class.  We deserve to have very strong pets just as mages do.  Does that mean pets that are equal in every apsect?  No, it does not, when you factor in the beastlord abilites that benefit pets (buffs/slow) then use that as a basis for balancing the mage pets.  Both should end up tanking about the same, when you factor in those considerations.  That does not mean that "mage pets should tank way better than beastlord pets."  Nor vice versa (as it currently stands now.<br />_________________<br />Churizo Andeggs
