<span style="text-decoration: underline">Dev-Corner:</span>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Let's nail down some terminology, for everyone's sake. I'll edit Rich to make sure he follows the same terminology. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Pure Caster means any non-hybrid, non-melee (Necromancer, Magician, Enchanter, Wizard, Cleric, Druid and Shaman). 
<br />

<br />
Int Caster are Necromancers, Magicians, Enchanters and Wizards. 
<br />

<br />
Wis Casters (or Priests) are Clerics, Druids and Shamans. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Hybrids are Bards (though they will probably have to be considered separately for most things), Rangers, Paladins, Shadowknights and Beastlords. </span>
<br />

<br />
Melee are Monks, Rogues and Warriors. 
<br />

<br />
Alan
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
