<br />

<br />
for myself, as a mage since aug of 1999 (yes the glory days and the days of hell, still lvoe playing the mage).  my pet is my defense.  i have little to no defensive skills otherwise (phear my 1hb of 115, ac of spun glass, armor of silk).  as a mage, i see myself , well not quite hiding behind fluffy, but behind fluffy nuking down the mobs.
<br />

<br />
how i see the bl is a bit different.  not worse, just different.  i have a couple bl twinks, but they are little (14? 20?) so in no way can i speak for the class, but from how my friends play, it is more of a partnership between the bl and the pet, with you tanking along side your pet.  in a lot of cases, i hear that the bl tanks more than the pet does.  
<br />

<br />
this is why, i feel that the mage pets really should be better than the bl pets.  my pet is supposed to be my shield, allowing me to burn mobs down.  whereas, the bl pet is more of a direct partner in crime.  it would seem to me to be unfair to have your pet the same as mine AND you can tank along side him.
<br />

<br />
just my couple of coppers of thought on this issue.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.neriak.com/rhy-sig1202.jpg" border="0" /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=827700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Rhy is a very Rhy-y Rhy</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
