			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Little hint, but in order to make this post hold any validity over the whole issue, you'd have to actually play a Bst.  If you played a Bst since SoL was released (as I have) you would realize that Bst pet tuning was going on the better part of a year, and as of the time this post was written, Bst pets were in their final stages of being tuned from the broken stage they started in.  They underwent a completly different tuning route than the re-tuning that happened with the mage and necro classes.
<br />

<br />
After this 'pet tuning' took place, Bst pets recieved a few more minor tweaks that the devs deemed 'balanced' with the other pet classes (even if you insist on attempting to include us with 'minor pet classes' heh heh).  Also you have to realize that further pet tuning took place when developing the Planes of Power expansion in regards to major and minor pet classes alike, which wasn't released untill October of 2002 (after this post, so 61+ pets have nothing to do with it).
<br />

<br />
During the SoL era, summoned pets were actually viable tanks/offtanks for SoL content mobs and previous expansion mobs.  The issue of mages not having effective pets to tank current NPC's didn't arise untill PoP was actually released.  Seeing as this post has nothing to do with PoP to today's content, it still doesn't cover the issues you are trying to get across.  Mage pets are in the process of being retuned, this we all know, and hopefully we will all be able to come to a common balance here where the majority of mages are happy about the upgrades that are made.
<br />

<br />
If you insist on grouping us with the 'minor' pet classes as this post may imply, so be it.  However, it doesn't change the fact that the pet is obviously major enough for some mages to take notice of.  Regardless of what the PR people make statements of, the fact remains that Bsts are considered 1 of the 3 major pet classes due to pet buffs, control, pet DPS and overall pet power.  That and typically the PR people only know whatever the devs decide to tell them, very few have intimate class knowledge of all classes.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Elder Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
